  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `22A. Offences by companies.`
  line `22B. Offences by societies or trusts.`
  line `22C. Punishment for offences by companies, societies or trusts.`
  line `23. Enhanced penalties.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `F ORFEITURE OF PROCEEDS OF TERRORISM OR ANY PROPERTY INTENDED TO BE`
  line `USED FOR TERRORISM`
  line `24. Reference to proceeds of terrorism to include any property intended to be used for terrorism.`
  line `24A. Forfeiture of proceeds of terrorism.`
  line `25. Powers of investigating officer and Designated Authority and appeal a gainst order of Designated`
  line Authority.
  line `26. Court to order forfeiture of proceeds of terrorism.`
  line `27. Issue of show cause notice before forfeiture of proceeds of terrorism.`
  line `28. Appeal.`
  line `29. Order of forfeiture not to Interfere with other punishments.`
  line `30. Claims by third party.`
  line `31. Powers of Designated Authority.`
  line `32. Certain transfers to be null and void.`
  line `33. Forfeiture of property of certain persons.`
  line `34. Company to transfer shares to Government.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `TERRORIST ORGANISATIONS AND INDIVIDUALS`
  line `35. Amendment of Schedule, etc.`
  line `36. Denotification of terrorist organisation or individual.`
  line `37. Review Committees.`
  line `38. Offence relating to membership of a terrorist organisation`
  line `39. Offence relating to support given to a terrorist organisation.`
  line `40. Offence of r aising fund for a terrorist organisation.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `41. Continuance of association.`
  line `42. Power to delegate.`
  line `43. Officers competent to investigate offence under Chapters IV and VI.`
  line `43A. Power to arrest, search, etc.`
  line `43B. Procedure of arrest, seizure, etc.`
  line `43C. Application of provisions of Code.`
  line `43D. Modified application of certain provisions of the Code.`
