obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `THE UNLAWFUL ACTIVITIES (PREVENTION) ACT, 1967`
  line `A CT N O. 37 OF 1967`
  line `[30 th December, 1967. ]`
  line `An Act to provide for the more effective prevention of certain unlawful activities of individuals`
  line `and associations 1 [, and for dealing with terrorist activities, ] and for matters connected`
  line therewith.
  line `2 [W HEREAS the Security Council of the United Nations in its 4385th meeting adopted Resolution`
  line `1373 (2001) on 28th September, 2001, under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United Nations requiring`
  line `all the States to take measures to combat international terrorism;`
  line `A N D WHEREAS Resolutions 1267 (1999), 1333 (2000), 1363 (2001), 1390 (2002), 1455 (2003), 1526`
  line `(2004), 1566 (2004), 1617 (2005), 1735 (2006) and 1822 (2008) of the Security Council of the United`
  line `Nations require the States to take action against certain terrorists and t errorist organisations, to freeze the`
  line `assets and other economic resources, to prevent the entry into or the transit through their territory, and`
  line `prevent the direct or indirect supply, sale or transfer of arms and ammunitions to the individuals or`
  line `entities listed in the Schedule;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS the Central Government, in exercise of the powers conferred by section 2 of the`
  line `United Nations (Security Council) Act, 1947 (43 of 1947) has made the Prevention and Suppression of`
  line `Terrorism (Implementation of Security Co uncil Resolutions) Order, 2007;`
  line `A ND WHEREAS it is considered necessary to give effect to the said Resolutions and the Order and to`
  line `make special provisions for the prevention of, and for coping with, terrorist activities and for matters`
  line `connected therewith or incidental thereto.]`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Eighteenth Year of t he Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `3 [ 1. Short title, extent and application. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the U nlawful Activities`
  line `(Prevention) Act, 1967 (37 of 1967).`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) Every person shall be liable to punishment under this Act for every act or omission contrary to the`
  line `provisions thereof, of which he is held guilty in India.`
  line `( 4 ) Any person, who commits an offence bey ond India, which is punishable under this Act, shall be`
  line `dealt with according to the provisions of this Act in the same manner as if such act had been committed in`
  line India.
  line `( 5 ) The provi sions of this Act apply also to —`
  line `( a ) citizens of India outside India;`
  line `( b ) persons in the service of the Government, wherever they may be; and`
  line `( c ) persons on ships and aircrafts, registered in India, wherever they may be.`
  line `2. Definitions. — ( 1 ) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “ association ” means any combination or body of individuals;`
  line `( b ) “ cession of a part of the territory of India ” includes admission of the claim of any f oreign`
  line `country to any such part;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 2004, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 2 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 2004, s. 4, for section s 1, 2, 2A (w.e.f 21 - 9 - 2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
