  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  sourcePage 5
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line 5
  line `( c ) “ Code ” means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973(2 of 1974);`
  line `( d ) “ court ” means a criminal court having jurisdiction, under the Code, to try offences under this`
  line `Act 1 [and includes a Special Court constituted under section 11 or under 2 [section 22] of the National`
  line `Investigation Agency Act, 2008];`
  line `( e ) “ Designated Authority ” means such officer of the Central Government not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Secretary to that Government, or such officer of the State Government not below the rank of`
  line `Secretary to that Government, as the case may be, as may be specified by the Central Gover nment or`
  line `the State Government, by notification pu blished in the Official Gazette;`
  line `3 [( ea ) “ economic security ” includes financial, monetary and fiscal stability, security of means of`
  line `production and distribution, food security, livelihood security, energy security, ecological and`
  line `environmental security;]`
  line `1 [ 4 [( eb )] “ Order ” means the Prevention and Suppression of Ter rorism (Implementation of`
  line `Security Council Resolutions) Order, 2007, as may be amended from time to time;]`
  line `2 [( ec ) “ person ” includes —`
  line `( i ) an individual,`
  line `( ii ) a company,`
  line `( iii ) a firm,`
  line `( iv ) an organisation or an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not,`
  line `( v ) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub - clauses, and`
  line `( vi ) any agency, office or branch owned or controlled by any person falling within any of the`
  line `preceding sub - clauses;]`
  line `( f ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `5 [ ( g ) “ proceeds of terrorism ” means, —`
  line `( i ) all kinds of properties which have been derived or obtained from commission of any`
  line `terrorist act or have been acquired through funds traceable to a terrorist act, irrespective of person`
  line `in whose name such proceeds are standing or in whose possession they are found; or`
  line `( ii ) any property which is being used, or is intended to be used, for a terrorist act or for the`
  line `purpose of an individual terrorist or a terrorist gang or a terrorist organisation.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this Act, it is hereby declared that the expression`
  line `“ proceeds of terrorism ” includes any property intended to be used for terrorism;]`
  line `6 [( h ) “ property ” means property and assets of every description whether corporeal or incorporeal,`
  line `movable or immovable, tangible or intangible and legal documents, deeds and 7 [instruments in any`
  line `form including but not limited to] electronic or digital, evi dencing title to, or interest in, such property`
  line `or assets by means of bank credits, travellers ’ cheques, bank cheques, money orders, shares,`
  line `securities, bonds, drafts, letters of credit, cash and bank account including fund, however acquired;`
  line `( ha ) “ Schedule ” means 8 [ a Schedule] to this Act;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 3 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 2 for “section 21” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Clause ( ea ) renumbered clause ( eb ) thereof by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause ( g ) (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 3, for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 2, for “instruments in any form including” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 2 for “ the Schedul e ” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-6
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Page 6`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `( i ) “ secession of a part of the territory of India from the Union ” includes the assertion of any`
  line `claim to determine whether such part will remain a part of the territory of India;`
  line `( j ) “ State Government ”, in relat ion to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof;`
  line `( k ) “ terrorist act ” has the meaning assigned to it in section 15, and the expressions “ terrorism ”`
  line `and “ terrorist ” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `( l ) “ terrorist gang ” means any association, other than terrorist organisation, whether systematic or`
  line `otherwise, which is concerned with, or involved in, terrorist act;`
  line `( m ) “ terrorist organisation ” means an organisation listed in the 1 [First Schedule ] or an`
  line `organisation operat ing under the same name as an organisation so listed;`
  line `( n ) “ Tribunal ” means the Tribunal constituted under section 5;`
  line `( o ) “ unlawful activity ”, in relation to an individual or association, means any action taken by such`
  line `individual or association (whether by committing an act or by words, either spoken or written, or by`
  line `signs or by visible representation or otherwise), —`
  line `( i ) which is intended, or supports any claim, to bring about, on any ground whatsoever, the`
  line `cession of a part of the territory of India or the secession of a part of the territory of India from`
  line `the Union, or which incites any individual or group of individuals to bring about such cession or`
  line `secession; or`
  line `( ii ) which disclaims, questions, disrupts or is intended to disrupt the sovereignty and`
  line `terr itorial integrity of India; or`
  line `( iii ) which causes or is intended to cause disaffection against India;`
  line `( p ) “ unlawful association ” means any association, —`
  line `( i ) which has for its object any unlawful activity, or which encourages or aids persons to`
  line `undertake an y unlawful activity, or of which the members undertake such activity; or`
  line `( ii ) which has for its object any activity which is punishable under section 153A (45 of 1860)`
  line `or section 153B of the Indian Penal Code, or which encourages or aids persons to undertake any`
  line `such activity, or of which the members undertake any such activity:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in sub - clause ( ii ) shall apply to the State of Jammu and Kashmir;`
  line `( q ) words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Code shall have the`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in the Code.`
  line `( 2 ) Any reference in this Act to any enactment or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an area in`
  line `which such enactment or such provision is not in force, be construed as a r eference to the corresponding`
  line `law or the relevant provision of the corresponding law, if any, in force in that area. ]`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `U NLAWFUL ASSOCIATION S`
  line `3. Declaration of an association as unlawful. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is of opinion that any`
  line `association is, or has become, an unlawful association, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare such association to be unlawful.`
  line `( 2 ) Every such notification shall specify the grounds on which it is issued and such other particulars`
  line `as the Central Government may consider necessary:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub - section shall require the Central Government to disclose any fact`
  line `which it considers to be against the public interest to disclose.`
  line `( 3 ) No such notification shall have effect until the Tribunal has, by an order made under section 4,`
  line `confirmed the declaration made therein and the order is published in the Official Gazette:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 2 for “Sched ule” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of opinion that circumstances exist which render it`
  line `necessary fo r that Government to declare an association to be unlawful with immediate effect, it may, for`
  line `reasons to be stated in writing, direct that the notification shall, subject to any order that may be made`
  line `under section 4, have effect from the date of its publi cation in the Official Gazette.`
  line `( 4 ) Every such notification shall, in addition to its publication in the Official Gazette, be published in`
  line `not less than one daily newspaper having circulation in the State in which the principal office, if any, of`
  line `the assoc iation affected is situated, and shall also be served on such association in such manner as the`
  line `Central Government may think fit and all or any of the following modes may be followed in effecting`
  line `such service, namely: —`
  line `( a ) by affixing a copy of the notification to some conspicuous part of the office, if any, of the`
  line `association; or`
  line `( b ) by serving a copy of the notification, where possible, on the principal office - bearers, if any,`
  line `of the association; or`
  line `( c ) by proclaiming by beat of drum or by means of loudspeakers, the contents of the notification`
  line `in the area in which the activities of the association are ordinarily carried on; or`
  line `( d ) in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
  line `4. Reference to Tribunal. — ( 1 ) Where any association has been declared unlawful by a notification`
  line `issued under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3, the Central Government shall, within thirty days from the date`
  line `of the publication of the notification under the said sub - section, refer the notification to the Tribunal for`
  line `the purpose o f adjudicating whether or not there is sufficient cause for declaring the association unlawful.`
  line `( 2 ) On receipt of a reference under sub - section ( 1 ), the Tribunal shall call upon the association`
  line `affected by notice in writing to show cause, within thirty days from the date of the service of such notice,`
  line `why the association should not be declared unlawful.`
  line `( 3 ) After considering the cause, if any, shown by the association or the office - bearers or members`
  line `thereof, the Tribunal shall hold an inquiry in the man ner specified in section 9 and after calling for such`
  line `further information as it may consider necessary from the Central Government or from any office - bearer`
  line `or member of the association, it shall decide whether or not there is sufficient cause for declarin g the`
  line `association to be unlawful and make, as expeditiously as possible and in any case within a period of six`
  line `months from the date of the issue of the notification under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 3, such order as it`
  line `may deem fit either confirming the dec laration made in the notification or cancelling the same.`
  line `( 4 ) The order of the Tribunal made under sub - section ( 3 ) shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
  line `5. Tribunal. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute, as`
  line `and when necessary, a t ribunal to be known as the “ Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Tribunal ” consisting`
  line `of one person, to be appo inted by the Central Government:`
  line `Provided that no person shall be so appointed unless he is a Judge of a High Court.`
  line `( 2 ) If, for any reason, a vacancy (other than a temporary absence) occurs in the office of the presiding`
  line `officer of the Tribunal, then, the Central Government shall appoint another person in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this section to fill the vacancy an d the proceedings may be continued before the Tribunal`
  line `from the stage at which the vacancy is filled.`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government shall make available to the Tribunal such staff as may be necessary for`
  line `the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line `( 4 ) All expenses incurred in connection with the Tribunal shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated`
  line `Fund of India.`
  line `( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of section 9, the Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure`
  line `in all matters arising out of the discharge o f its functions including the place or places at which it will`
  line `hold its sittings.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `( 6 ) The Tribunal shall, for the purpose of making an inquiry under this Act, have the same powers as`
  line `are vested in a c ivil c ourt under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in`
  line `respect o f the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line `( b ) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line `( c ) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line `( d ) the requisitioning of any public record from any c ourt or office;`
  line `( e ) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line `( 7 ) Any proceeding before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Tribunal shall be deemed`
  line `to be a c ivil c ourt for the purposes of section 195 and 1 [ Chapter XXVI] of the 2 [Code].`
  line `6. Period of operation and cancellation of notification. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub -`
  line `section ( 2 ), a notification issued under section 3 shall, if the declaration made therein is confirmed by the`
  line `Tribunal by an order made under section 4, remain in f orce for a period of 3 [five years] from the date on`
  line `which the notification becomes effective.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), the Central Government may, either on its`
  line `own motion or on the application of any person aggrieved, at any time, cancel the notification issued`
  line `under section 3, whether or not the declaration made therein has been confirmed by the Tribunal.`
  line `7. Power to prohibit the use of funds of an unlawful association. — ( 1 ) Where an association has`
  line `been declared unlawful by a notification issued under section 3 which has become effective under sub -`
  line `section ( 3 ) of that section and the Central Government is satisfied, after such inquiry as it may think it,`
  line `that any person has custody of any moneys, securities or credits which are being used or are intended to`
  line `be used for the purpose of the unlawful association, the Central Government may, by order in writing,`
  line `prohibit such person from paying, delivering, transferring or otherwise dealing in any manner whatsoever`
  line `with such mone ys, securities or credits or with any other moneys, securities or credits which may come`
  line `into his custody after the making of the order, save in accordance with the written orders of the Central`
  line `Government and a copy of such order shall be served upon the person so prohibited in the manner`
  line `specified in sub - section ( 3 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government may endorse a copy of the prohibitory order made under sub - section ( 1 )`
  line `for investigation to any gazette o fficer of the Government it may select, and such copy shall be a warrant`
  line `where under such officer may enter in or upon any premises of the person to whom the order is directed,`
  line `examine the books of such person, search for moneys, securities or credits, and make inquiries from such`
  line `person or any officer, agent or s ervant of such person, touching the origin of any dealings in any moneys,`
  line `securities or credits which the i nvestigating o fficer may suspect are being used or are intended to be used`
  line `for the purpose of the unlawful association.`
  line `( 3 ) A copy of an order made u nder this section shall be served in the manner provided in the 2 [Code],`
  line `for the service of a summons, or where the person to be served is a corporation, company, bank or other`
  line `association, it shall be served on any secretary, director or other officer or person concerned with the`
  line `management thereof, or by leaving it or sending it by post addressed to the corporation, company, bank or`
  line `other association at its registered office, or where there is no registered office, at the place where it carries`
  line `on busines s.`
  line `( 4 ) Any person aggrieved by a prohibitory order made under sub - section ( 1 ) may, within fifteen days`
  line `from the date of the service of such order, make an application to the Court of the District Judge within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction such per son voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2004, s. 5, for “Chapter XXXV” (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “ Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)” (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 3, for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-9
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Page 9`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  sourcePage 9
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line 9
  line `works for gain, to establish that the moneys, securities or credits in respect of which the prohibitory order`
  line `has been made are not being used or are not intended to be used for the purpose of th e unlawful`
  line `association and the Court of the District Judge shall decide the question.`
  line `( 5 ) Except so far as is necessary for the purposes of any proceedings under this section, no`
  line `information obtained in the course of any investigation made under sub - sectio n ( 2 ) shall be divulged by`
  line `any gazette o fficer of the Government, without the consent of the Central Government.`
  line `( 6 ) In this section, “ security ” includes a document whereby any person acknowledges that he is under`
  line `a legal liability to pay money, or where under any person obtains a legal right to the payment of money.`
  line `8. Power to notify places used for the purpose of an unlawful association. — ( 1 ) Where an`
  line `association has been declared unlawful by a notification issued under section 3 which has become`
  line `effecti ve under sub - section ( 3 ) of that section, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, notify any place which in its opinion is used for the purpose of such unlawful association.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub - section, “ place ” includes a house or building, or part`
  line `thereof, or a tent or vessel.`
  line `( 2 ) On the issue of a notification under sub - section ( 1 ), the District Magistrate within the local limits`
  line `of whose jurisdiction such notified place is situate or any officer authori sed by him in writing in this`
  line `behalf shall make a list of all movable properties (other than wearing - apparel, cooking vessels, beds and`
  line `beddings, tools of artisans, implements of husbandry, cattle, grain and food - stuffs and such other articles`
  line `as he consid ers to be of a trivial nature) found in the notified place in the presence of two respectable`
  line witnesses.
  line `( 3 ) If, in the opinion of the District Magistrate, any articles specified in the list are or may be used for`
  line `the purpose of the unlawful association, h e may make an order prohibiting any person from using the`
  line `articles save in accordance with the written orders of the District Magistrate.`
  line `( 4 ) The District Magistrate may thereupon make an order that no person who at the date of the`
  line `notification was not a r esident in the notified place shall, without the permission of the District`
  line `Magistrate, enter, or be on or in, the notified place:`
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub - section shall apply to any near relative of any person who was a`
  line `resident in the notified p lace at the date of the notification.`
  line `( 5 ) Where in pursuance of sub - section ( 4 ), any person is granted permission to enter, or to be on or in,`
  line `the notified place, that person shall, while acting under such permission, comply with such orders for`
  line `regulating his conduct as may be given by the District Magistrate.`
  line `( 6 ) Any police officer, not below the rank of a sub - inspector, or any other person authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government may search any person entering, or seeking to enter, or being on or in,`
  line `the notified place and may detain any such person for the purpose of sea rching him:`
  line `Provided that no female shall be searched in pursuance of this sub - section except by a female.`
  line `( 7 ) If any person is in the notified place in contravention of an order made under sub - section ( 4 ), then,`
  line `without prejudice to any other proceedings which may be taken against him, he may be removed`
  line `therefrom by any off icer or by any other person authorised in this behalf by the Central Government.`
  line `( 8 ) Any person aggrieved by a notification issued in respect of a place under sub - section ( 1 ) or by an`
  line `order made under sub - section ( 3 ) or sub - section ( 4 ) may, within thirty d ays from the date of the`
  line `notification or order, as the case may be, make an application to the Court of the District Judge within the`
  line `local limits of whose jurisdiction such notified place is situate —`
  line `( a ) for declaration that the place has not been used fo r the purpose of the unlawful association; or`
  line `( b ) for setting aside the order made under sub - section ( 3 ) or sub - section ( 4 ),`
  line `and on receipt of the application the Court of the District Judge shall, after giving the parties an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, de cide the question.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-10
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Page 10`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  sourcePage 10
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `9. Procedure to be followed in the disposal of applications under this Act. — Subject to any rules`
  line `that may be made under this Act, the procedure to be followed by the Tribunal in holding any inquiry`
  line `under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 4 or by a Court of the District Judge in disposing of any application under`
  line `sub - section ( 4 ) of section 7 or sub - section ( 8 ) of section 8 shall, so far as may be, be the procedure laid`
  line `down in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the investigation of claims and the decision of`
  line `the Tribunal or the Court of the District Judge, as the case may be, shall be final.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `O FFENCES AND PENALTIES`
  line `1 [ 10. Penalty for being member of an unlawful association, etc. — Where an association is declared`
  line `unlawful by a notification issued under section 3 which has become effective under s ub - section ( 3 ) of that`
  line `section, —`
  line `( a ) a person, who —`
  line `( i ) is and continues to be a member of such association; or`
  line `( ii ) takes part in meetings of such association; or`
  line `( iii ) contributes to, or receives or solicits any contribution for the purpose of, such`
  line `association; or`
  line `( iv ) in any way assists the operations of such association,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, and shall also b e liable`
  line `to fine; and`
  line `( b ) a person, who is or continues to be a member of such association, or voluntarily does an act`
  line `aiding or promoting in any manner the objects of such association and in either case is in possession`
  line `of any unlicensed firearms, ammunit ion, explosive or other instrument or substance capable of`
  line `causing mass destruction and commits any act resulting in loss of human life or grievous injury to any`
  line `person or causes sign ificant damage to any property, —`
  line `( i ) and if such act has resulted in the death of any person, shall be punishable with death or`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.]
  line `11. Penalty for dealing with funds of an unlawful association. — If any person on whom a`
  line `prohibitory order has been served under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 7 in respect of any moneys, securities`
  line `or credits pays, delivers, transfers or otherwise deals in any manner whatsoever with the same in`
  line `contravention of the prohibitory order, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three years, or with fine, or with both, and notwithstanding anything contained in the 2 [ Code ],`
  line `the court trying such contravention may also impose on the person convicted an additional fine to recover`
  line `from him the amount of the moneys or credits or the market value of the securities in respect of which the`
  line `prohibitory order has been contravened or such part thereof as the court may deem fit.`
  line `12. Penalty for contravention of an order made in respect of a notified place. — ( 1 ) Whoever uses`
  line `any article in contravention of a proh ibitory order in respect thereof made under sub - section ( 3 ) of section`
  line `8 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, and shall also be liable`
  line `to fine.`
  line `( 2 ) Whoever knowingly and wilfully is in, or effects or attempts to ef fect entry into, a notified place`
  line `in contravention of an order made under sub - section ( 4 ) of section 8 shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2004, s. 6, for section 10 (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for “C ode of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)” (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-11
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Page 11`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  sourcePage 11
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `13. Punishment for unlawful activities. — ( 1 ) Whoever —`
  line `( a ) takes part in or commits, or`
  line `( b ) advocates, abets, advises or incites the commission of, any unlawful activity, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to seven years and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line `( 2 ) Whoever, in any way, assists any unlawful activity of any association, declared unlawful under`
  line `section 3, after the notification by which it has been so declared has become effective under sub - section`
  line `( 3 ) of that section, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years, or`
  line `with fine, or with both.`
  line `( 3 ) Nothing in this section shall apply to any treaty, agreement or convention entered into between the`
  line `Government of India and the Government of any other country or to any negotiations th ere for carried on`
  line `by any person authorised in this behalf by the Government of India.`
  line `14. Offences to be cognizable. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the 1 [Code], an offence`
  line `punishable under this Act shall be cognizable.`
  line `2 [ CHAPTER IV`
  line `P UNISHMENT FOR TERRORIST ACTIVITIES`
  line `3 [ 15. Terrorist act. — 4 [( 1 )] Whoever does any act with intent to threaten or likely to threaten the`
  line `unity, integrity, security 5 [, economic security,] or sovereignty of India or with intent to strike terror or`
  line `likely to strike terror in the people or any section of the people in India or in any foreign country, —`
  line `( a ) by using bombs, dynamite or other explosive substances or inflammable substances or`
  line `firearms or other lethal weapons or poisonous or noxious gases or other chemicals or by any other`
  line `substances (whether biological radioactive, nuclear or other wise) of a hazardous nature or by any`
  line `other means of whatever nature to cause or likely to cause —`
  line `( i ) death of, or injuries to, any person or persons; or`
  line `( ii ) loss of, or damage to, or destruction of, property; or`
  line `( iii ) disruption of any supplies or servic es essential to the life of the community in India or in`
  line `any foreign country; or`
  line `5 [( iiia ) damage to, the monetary stability of India by way of production or smuggling or`
  line `circulation of high quality counterfeit Indian paper currency, coin or of any other ma terial; or]`
  line `( iv ) damage or destruction of any property in India or in a foreign country used or intended to`
  line `be used for the defence of India or in connection with any other purposes of the Government of`
  line `India, any State Government or any of their agencies; or`
  line `( b ) overawes by means of criminal force or the show of criminal force or attempts to do so or`
  line `causes death of any public functionary or attempts to cause death of any public functionary; or`
  line `( c ) detains, kidnaps or abducts any person and threatens to kill or injure such person or does any`
  line `other act in order to compel the Government of India, any State Government or the Government of a`
  line `foreign country or 6 [an international or inter - governmental organisation or any other person to do or`
  line `abstain from doing any act; or]`
  line `commits a terrorist act.`
  line `7 [ Explanation. — For the purpose of this sub - section, —`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 29 of 2004, s. 3, for “ Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 18 98)” (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for Chapter IV (w.e.f. 21 - 9 - 2004).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 4, for section 15 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `4. Section 15 r enumbered as sub - section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 3 of 2013, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013 ).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for “any other person to do or abstain from doing any act,” ( w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `7. S ubs. by s. 4, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-12
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Page 12`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  sourcePage 12
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `( a ) “ public functionary ” means the constitutional authorities or any other functionary notified in`
  line `the O fficial Gazette by the Central Government as public functionary;`
  line `( b ) “ high quality counterfeit Indian currency ” means the counterfeit currency as may be declared`
  line `after examination by an authorised or notified forensic authority that such currency imitates or`
  line `compromises with the key security features as specified in the Third Schedule.]`
  line `1 [( 2 ) The terrorist act includes an act which constitutes an offence within the scope of, and as defined`
  line `in any of the treaties specified in the Second Schedule.]`
  line `16. Punishment for t errorist a ct. — ( 1 ) Whoever commits a terrorist act shall, —`
  line `( a ) if such act has resulted in the death of any person, be punishable with death or imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `five years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `16 A. [ Punishment for making demands of radioactive substances, nuclear devices, etc. ] Omitted by`
  line `the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Amendment ( Repealing and Amending ) Act 2013 ( 3 of 2013 ),`
  line `s. 5 ( w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013 ).`
  line `2 [ 17. Punishment for r aising f und s for t errorist a ct. — Whoever, in India or in a foreign country,`
  line `directly or indirectly, raises or provides funds or collects funds, whether from a legitimate or illegitimate`
  line `source, from any person or persons or attempts to provide to, or raises or collects funds for any perso n or`
  line `persons, knowing that such funds are likely to be used, in full or in part by such person or persons or by a`
  line `terrorist organisation or by a terrorist gang or by an individual terrorist to commit a terrorist act,`
  line `notwithstanding whether such funds were actually used or not for commission of such act, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this section, —`
  line `( a ) participating, organising or directing in any of the acts stated therein shall constitute an`
  line offence;
  line `( b ) raising funds shall include raising or collecting or providing funds through production or`
  line `smuggling or circulation of high quality cou nterfeit Indian currency; and`
  line `( c ) raising or collecting or providing funds, in any manner for the benefit of, or, to an individual`
  line `terrorist, terrorist gang or terrorist organisation for the purpose not specifically covered under section`
  line `15 shall also be c onstrued as an offence.]`
  line `18. Punishment for c onspiracy, etc. — Whoever conspires or attempts to commit, or advocates,`
  line `abets, advises or 3 [incites, directly or knowingly facilitates] the commission of, a terrorist act or any act`
  line `preparatory to the commission of a terrorist act, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `shall not be less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to`
  line fine.
  line `4 [ 18A. Punishment for organi s ing of terrorist camps. — Whoever organ ises or causes to be`
  line `organised any camp or camps for imparting training in terrorism shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall`
  line `also be liable to fine.`
  line `1 8B. Punishment for recruiting of any person or persons for terrorist act. — Whoever recruits or`
  line `causes to be recruited any person or persons for commission of a terrorist act shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for section 17 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 7, for “incites or knowingly facilitates” (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-13
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Page 13`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `19. Punishment for h arbouring, etc. — Whoever voluntarily harbours or conceals, or attempts to`
  line `harbour or conceal any person knowing that such person is a terrorist shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three years but which may extend to imprisonment`
  line `for life, and shall also be liable to fine:`
  line `Provided that this sec tion shall not apply to any case in which the harbour or concealment is by the`
  line `spouse of the offender.`
  line `20. Punishment for b eing m ember of t errorist g ang or o rganisation. — Any person who is a`
  line `member of a terrorist gang or a terrorist organisation, which is i nvolved in terrorist act, shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line `21. Punishment for h olding p roceeds of t errorism. — Whoever knowingly holds any property`
  line `derived or obtain ed from commission of any terrorist act or acquired through the terrorist fund shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to imprisonment for life, and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine.`
  line `22. Punishment for threatening w itness. — Whoever threatens any person who is a witness or any`
  line `other person in whom such witness may be interested, with violence, or wrongfully restrains or confines`
  line `the witness, or any other person in whom the witness may be interested, or does any other unlawful act`
  line `with intent to cause any of the said acts, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to`
  line `three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `1 [ 22A. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person (including promoters of the company) who, at the time the offence was`
  line `committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the`
  line `company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and s hall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person (including`
  line `promoters) liable to any punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committ ed`
  line `without his knowledge or that he had exercised reasonable care to prevent the commission of such`
  line offence.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that th e offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any neglect on the pa rt of, any promoter, director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer of the company, such promoter, director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordi ngly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ company ” means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line `( b ) “ director ”, in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
  line `22B. Offences by societies or trusts. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `society or trust, every person (including the promoter of society or settlor of the trust) who at the time the`
  line `offence was committed was in charge of, and was res ponsible to, the society or trust for the conduct of the`
  line `business of the society or the trust, as well as the society or trust, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub - section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised reasonable care to prevent the commission of such offen ce.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a society or trust and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013 ).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-14
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Page 14`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  sourcePage 14
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to, any negl ect on the part of any promoter, director, manager, secretary,`
  line `trustee or other officer of the society or trust, such promoter, director, manager, secretary, trustee or other`
  line `officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ society ” means any body corporate registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21`
  line `of 1860) or any other State Act governing the registration of societies;`
  line `( b ) “ trust ” means any body registered under the Indian Trusts Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) or any other`
  line `State Act governing the registration of trusts;`
  line `( c ) “ director ”, in relation to a society or trust, means a member of its governing board other than`
  line `an ex officio member representing the interests of the Central or State Government or the appropriate`
  line `statutory authority.]`
  line `22C. Punishment for offences by companies, societies or trusts. — Where any offence under the`
  line `Act has been committed by a company or a society or a trust, as the case may be, every person (including`
  line `promoter of company or trust or settlor of the trust) who at the time of the offence was either in charge or`
  line `responsible for the conduct of the business shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than seven years but which may extend to imprisonment for life and shall also be liable with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than five crore rupees and which may extend to ten crore rupees.]`
  line `23. Enhanced p enalties. — ( 1 ) 1 [If any person with intent to aid any terrorist or terrorist organisation`
  line `or a terrorist gang contravenes] any provision of, or any rule made under the Explosives Act, 1884(4 of`
  line `1884) or the Explosive Substances Act, 1908(6 of 1908) or the Inflammable Subs tances Act, 1952(20 of`
  line `1952) or the Arms Act, 1959(54 of 1959), or is in unauthorised possession of any bomb, dynamite or`
  line `hazardous explosive substance or other lethal weapon or substance capable of mass destruction or`
  line `biological or 2 [chemical substance of warfare or high quality counterfeit Indian currency, he shall],`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any of the aforesaid Acts or the rules made thereunder, be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than five years but which may extend to`
  line `imprisonment for life, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `( 2 ) 3 [Any person who with the intent to aid any terrorist, or a terrorist o rganisation or a terrorist`
  line `gang ], attempts to contravene or abets, or does any act preparatory to contravention of any provision of`
  line `any law or rule specified in sub - section ( 1 ), shall be deemed to have contravened that provision under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ) and the provisions of that sub - section in relation to such person, have effect subject to the`
  line `modification that the ref erence to “ imprisonment for life ” therein shall be construed as a reference to`
  line `“ imprisonment for ten years ”.`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `F ORFEITURE OF PROCEEDS OF TERRORISM 4 [ OR ANY PROPERTY INTENDED TO BE USED`
  line `FOR TERRORISM ]`
  line `5 [ 24. Reference to proceeds of terrorism to include any property intended to be used for`
  line `terrorism. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, all references to “ proceeds of`
  line `terrorism ” shall include any property int ended to be used for terrorism.`
  line `24A. Forfeiture of proceeds of terrorism. — ( 1 ) No person shall hold or be in possession of any`
  line `proceeds of terrorism.`
  line `( 2 ) Proceeds of terrorism, whether held by a terrorist organisation or terrorist gang or by any other`
  line `person and whether or not such terrorist or other person is prosecuted or con victed for any offence under`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 9, for “If any person with intent to aid any terrorist contravenes” (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 8, for “chemical substance of warfare, he shall” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 9, for “ Any person who, with the intent to aid any terrorist” (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 10, ibid., for section 24 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-15
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Page 15`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `Chapter IV or Chapter VI, shall be liable to be forfeited to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, in the manner provided under this Chapter.`
  line `( 3 ) Where proceedings have been commenced under this se ction, the court may pass an order`
  line `directing attachment or forfeiture, as the case may be, of property equivalent to, or, the value of the`
  line `proceeds of terrorism involved in the offence.]`
  line `25. Powers of i nvestigating o fficer and Designated Authority and a ppeal a gainst o rder of`
  line `Designated Authority. — ( 1 ) If an officer investigating an offence committed under Chapter IV or`
  line `Chapter VI, has reason to believe that any property in relation to which an investigation is being`
  line `conducted, represents proceeds of terro rism, he shall, with the prior approval in writing of the Director`
  line `General of the Police of the State 1 [in which such property is situated, or where the investigation is`
  line `conducted by an officer of the National Investigation Agency, with the prior approval of the Director`
  line `General of National Investigation Agency, make an order] seizing such property and where it is not`
  line `practicable to seize such property, make an order of attachment directing that such property shall not be`
  line `transferred or otherwise dealt with except with the prior permission of the officer making such order, or of`
  line `the Designated Authority before whom the property seized or attached is produced and a copy of such`
  line `order shall be served on the person concerned.`
  line `( 2 ) The investigating officer shal l duly inform the Designated Authority within forty - eight hours of`
  line `the seizure or attachment of such property.`
  line `( 3 ) The Designated Authority before whom the seized or attached property is produced shall either`
  line `confirm or revoke the order of seizure or attachment so issued within a period of sixty days from the date`
  line `of such production:`
  line `Provided that an opportunity of making a representation by the person whose property is being seized`
  line `or attached shall be given.`
  line `( 4 ) In the case of immovable property atta ched by the investigating officer, it shall be deemed to have`
  line `been produced before the Designated Authority, when the investigating officer notifies his report and`
  line `places it at the disposal of the Designated Authority.`
  line `( 5 ) The investigating officer may sei ze and detain any cash to which this Chapter applies if he has`
  line `reasonable grounds for suspecting that —`
  line `( a ) it is intended to be used for the purposes of terrorism; or`
  line `( b ) it forms the whole or part of the resource s of a terrorist organisation:`
  line `Provided tha t the cash seized under this sub - section by the investigating officer shall be released`
  line `within a period of forty - eight hours beginning with the time when it is seized unless the matter involving`
  line `the cash is before the Designated Authority and such Authorit y passes an order allowing its retention`
  line `beyond forty - eight hours.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub - section, “ cash ” means —`
  line `( a ) coins or notes in any currency;`
  line `( b ) postal orders;`
  line `( c ) traveller ’ scheques;`
  line `2 [( ca ) credit or debit cards or cards that serve a similar purpose;]`
  line `( d ) banker ’ s drafts; and`
  line `( e ) such other monetary instruments as the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Government may specify by an order made in writing.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 3, for “ in which such property is situated, make an order ” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019)`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 11 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-16
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Page 16`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `( 6 ) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the Designat ed Authority may prefer an appeal to the`
  line `court within a period of thirty days from the date of receipt of the order, and the court may either confirm`
  line `the order of attachment of property or seizure so made or revoke such order and release the property.`
  line `26. Court to o rder f orfeiture of p roceeds of t errorism. — Where any property is seized or attached`
  line `on the ground that it constitutes proceeds of terrorism and the court confirms the order in this regard`
  line `under sub - section ( 6 ) of section 25, it may order forfeitu re of such property, whether or not the person`
  line `from whose possession it is seized or attached, is prosecuted in a court for an offence under Chapter IV or`
  line `Chapter VI.`
  line `27. Issue of s how c ause n otice before f orfeiture of p roceeds of t errorism. — ( 1 ) No order f orfeiting`
  line `any proceeds of terrorism shall be made under section 26 unless the person holding or in possession of`
  line `such proceeds is given a notice in writing informing him of the grounds on which it is proposed to forfeit`
  line `the proceeds of terrorism and such p erson is given an opportunity of making a representation in writing`
  line `within such reasonable time as may be specified in the notice against the grounds of forfeiture and is also`
  line `given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line `( 2 ) No order of for feiture shall be made under sub - section ( 1 ), if such person establishes that he is a`
  line `bona fide transferee of such proceeds for value without knowing that they represent proceeds of terrorism.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be competent for the court to make an order in respect of property seized or attached, —`
  line `( a ) directing it to be sold if it is a perishable property and the provisions of section 459 of the`
  line `Code shall, as nearly as may be practicable, apply to the net proceeds of such sale;`
  line `( b ) nominating any officer of the Central Government or the State Government, in the case of any`
  line `other property, to perform the function of the A dministrator of such property subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be specified by the court.`
  line `28. Appeal. — ( 1 ) Any person aggrieved by an order o f forfeiture under section 26 may, within one`
  line `month from the date of the receipt of such order, appeal to the High Court within whose jurisdiction, the`
  line `court, which passed the order appealed against, is situated.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an order under section 26 is modified or annulled by the High Court or where in a`
  line `prosecution instituted for any offence under Chapter IV or Chapter VI, the person against whom an order`
  line `of forfeiture has been made under section 26 is acquitted, such property shall be returned to him a nd in`
  line `either case if it is not possible for any reason to return the forfeited property, such person shall be paid the`
  line `price therefor as if the property had been sold to the Central Government with reasonable interest`
  line `calculated from the day of seizure of the property and such price shall be determined in the manner`
  line prescribed.
  line `29. Order of f orfeiture not to Interfere with other p unishments. — The order of forfeiture made`
  line `under this Chapter by the court, shall not prevent the infliction of any other punishmen t to which the`
  line `person affected thereby is liable under Chapter IV or Chapter VI.`
  line `30. Claims by t hird p arty. — ( 1 ) Where any claim is preferred or any objection is made to the seizure`
  line `or attachment of any property under section 25 on the ground that such prop er t y is not liable to seizure or`
  line `attachment, the Designated Authority before whom such property is produced, shall proceed to`
  line `investigate the claim or objection:`
  line `Provided that no such investigation shall be made where the Designated Authority considers that the`
  line `claim or objection is designed to cause unnecessary delay.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an appeal has been preferred under sub - section (6) of section 25 and any claimant or`
  line `objector establishes that the property specified in the notice issued under section 27 is not liable to be`
  line `forfeited under this Chapter, the said notice shall be withdrawn or modified accordingly.`
  line `31. Powers of Designated Authority. — The Designated Authority, acting under the provisions of`
  line `this Chapter, shall have all the powers of a civil court re quired for making a full and fair inquiry into the`
  line `matter before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-17
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Page 17`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  sourcePage 17
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `32. Certain t ransfers to be n ull and v oid. — Where, after the issue of an order under section 25 or`
  line `issue of a notice under section 27, any property referred to in the said order or notice is transferred by any`
  line `mode whatsoever, such transfer shall, for the purpose of the proceedings under this Chapter, be ignored`
  line `and if such property is subsequently forfeited, the transfer of such property shall be deemed to be null and`
  line void.
  line `33. Forfeiture of p roperty of c ertain p ersons. — ( 1 ) Where any person is accused of an offence`
  line `under Chapter IV or Chapter VI, it shall be open to the court to pass an order that all or any of the`
  line `properties, movable or immovable or both, belonging to him, shall, during the period of such trial, be`
  line `attache d, if not already attached under this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a person has been convicted of any offence punishable under Chapter IV or Chapter VI,`
  line `the court may, in addition to awarding any punishment, by order in writing, declare that any property,`
  line `movable or immovable or both, belonging to the accused and specified in the order, shall stand forfeited`
  line `to the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, free from all encumbrances.`
  line `1 [( 3 ) Where any person is accused of an offence concerning hig h quality counterfeit Indian currency,`
  line `the court may pass an order directing attachment or forfeiture, as the case may be, of property equivalent`
  line `to the value of such high quality counterfeit Indian currency involved in the offence including the face`
  line `value of such currency which are not defined to be of high quality, but are part of the common seizure`
  line `along with the high quality counterfeit Indian currency.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a person is accused of an offence punishable under Chapter IV or Chapter VI, the court`
  line `may pass an order directing attachment or forfeiture, as the case may be, of property equivalent to or the`
  line `value of the proceeds of terrorism involved in the offence.`
  line `( 5 ) Where any person is accused of an offence under Chapter IV or Chapter VI, it shall be ope n to the`
  line `court to pass an order that all or any of the property, movable or immovable or both, belonging to him`
  line `shall, where the trial under the Act cannot be concluded on account of the death of the accused or being`
  line `declared a proclaimed offender or for a ny other reason, be confiscated on the basis of material evidence`
  line `produced before the court.]`
  line `34. Company to t ransfer s hares to Government. — Where any share in a company stand forfeited to`
  line `the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, under this Chapter, then, the`
  line `company shall, on receipt of the order of the court, notwithstanding anything contai ned in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 ( 1 of 1956), or the articles of association of the company, forthwith register the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be, as the transferee of such share.`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `2 [TERRORIST ORGANISATIONS AND INDIVIDUALS]`
  line `35. Amendment of Schedule, etc. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by 3 [notification], in the`
  line `Official Gazette, —`
  line `( a ) add an organisation to the 4 [First Schedule] 5 [or the name of an individual in the Fourth`
  line Schedule];
  line `( b ) add also an organisation to the 4 [First Schedule], which is identified as a terrorist organisation`
  line `in a resolution adopted by the Security Council under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United`
  line `Nations, 5 [or the name of an individual in the Fourth Schedule], to combat international terrorism;`
  line `( c ) remove an organisation from the 4 [First Schedule] 5 [or t he name of an individual from the`
  line `Fourth Schedule];`
  line `( d ) amend the 4 [First Schedule] 5 [or the Fourth Schedule] in some other way.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Subs. by 28 of 2019, s. 4 for “ TERRORIST ORGANISATIONS” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 2013 s. 12, for “order” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for “Schedule” (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 28 of 2019 s. 5 (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-18
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Page 18`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  sourcePage 18
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `( 2 ) The Central Government shall exercise its power under clause ( a ) of sub - section ( 1 ) in respect of`
  line `1 [an organisation or an individual only if it believes that such organisation or individual is] involved in`
  line terrorism.
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub - section ( 2 ), 2 [an organisation or an individual shall be deemed to be`
  line `involved in terrorism if such organisation or individual ] —`
  line `( a ) commits or participates in acts of terrorism, or`
  line `( b ) prepares for terrorism, or`
  line `( c ) promotes or encourages terrorism, or`
  line `( d ) is otherwise involved in terrorism.`
  line `3 [( 4 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, add to or remove or amend`
  line `the Second Schedule or Third Schedule and thereupon the Second Schedule or the Third Schedule, as the`
  line `case may be, shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line `( 5 ) Every notification issued under sub - section ( 1 ) or sub - section ( 4 ) shal l, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is issued, be laid before Parliament.]`
  line `36. Denotification of 4 [terrorist organisation or individual]. — ( 1 ) An application may be made to`
  line `the Central Government for the exercise of its power under clause ( c ) of sub - section ( 1 ) of section 35 to`
  line `remove 5 [an organisation from the First Schedule, or as the case may be, the name of an individual from`
  line `the Fourth Schedule].`
  line `( 2 ) An application under sub - section ( 1 ) may be made by —`
  line `( a ) the organisation, or`
  line `( b ) any person affected by inclusion of the organisation in the 6 [First Schedule as a terrorist`
  line `organisation, or].`
  line `7 [( c ) any person affected by inclusion of his name in the Fourth Schedule as a terrorist.]`
  line `( 3 ) The Central Government may prescribe the procedure for admission and disposal of an`
  line `application made under this section.`
  line `( 4 ) Where an application under sub - section ( 1 ) has been rejected, the applicant may apply for a`
  line `review to the Review Committee constituted by the Central Government under sub - section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `37 within one month from the date of receipt of the order of such refusal by the applicant.`
  line `( 5 ) The Review Committee may allow an application for review against rejection, to remove 8 [an`
  line `organisation from the First Schedule or the name of an individual from the Fourth Schedule], if it`
  line `considers that the decision to reject was flawed when considered in the light of the principles applicable`
  line `on an application for judicial review.`
  line `( 6 ) Where the Review Co mmittee allows review under sub - section ( 5 ) by or in respect of 9 [or an`
  line `individual], it may make an order to such effect.`
  line `( 7 ) Where an order is made under sub - section (6), the Central Government shall, as soon as the`
  line `certified copy of the order is received by it, make an order removing the organisation from the 10 [First`
  line `Schedule or the name of an individual from the Fourth Schedule].`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 5, for “ an organisation only if it believes that it is” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for “ an organisation shall be deemed to be involved in terrorism if it” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 6, for “a terrorist organisation” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “ an organisation from the Schedule” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “ Schedule as a terrorist organization” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “ an organi sation from the Schedule” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `9. Ins. by s. 6, ibid., (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for “Schedule” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-19
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Page 19`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `37. Review Committees. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall constitute one or more Review`
  line `Committees for the purposes of section 36.`
  line `( 2 ) Every such Committee shall consist of a Chairperson and such other members not exceeding three`
  line `and possessing such qualifications as may be prescribed.`
  line `( 3 ) A Chairperson of the Committee shall be a person who is, or has been, a Judge of a High Cour t,`
  line `who shall be appointed by the Central Government and in the case of appointment of a sitting Judge, the`
  line `concurrence of the Chief Justice of the concerned High Court shall be obtained.`
  line `38. Offence r elating to m embership of a t errorist o rganisation. — ( 1 ) A person, who associates`
  line `himself, or professes to be associated, with a terrorist organisation with intention to further its activities,`
  line `commits an offence relating to membership of a terrorist organisation:`
  line `Provided that this sub - section shall not apply where the person charged is able to prove —`
  line `( a ) that the organisation was not declared as a terrorist organisation at the time when he became a`
  line `member or began to profess to be a member; and`
  line `( b ) that he has not taken part in the activities of the organisati on at any time during its inclusion in`
  line `the 1 [First Schedule] as a terrorist organisation.`
  line `( 2 ) A person, who commits the offence relating to membership of a terrorist organisation under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years, or with fine, or`
  line `with both.`
  line `39. Offence r elating to s upport g iven to a t errorist o rganisation. — ( 1 ) A person commits the`
  line `offence relating to support given to a terrorist organisation, —`
  line `( a ) who, with intention to further the activity of a terrorist organisation, —`
  line `( i ) invites support for the terrorist organization; and`
  line `( ii ) the support is not or is not restricted to provide money or other property within the`
  line `meaning of section 40;or`
  line `( b ) who, with intention to further the activity of a terrorist organisation, arranges, manages or`
  line `assists in arranging or managing a meeting which he knows is —`
  line `( i ) to support the terrorist organization; or`
  line `( ii ) to further the activity of the terrorist organization; or`
  line `( iii ) to bead dressed by a person who associates or professes to be associated with the terrorist`
  line `organisation; or`
  line `( c ) who, with intention to further the activity of a terrorist organisation, addresses a meeting`
  line `for the purpose of encouraging support for th e terrorist organisation or to further its activity.`
  line `( 2 ) A person, who commits the offen cerelating to support given to a terrorist organisation under sub -`
  line `section ( 1 ) shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding ten years, or with fine, or with`
  line both.
  line `40. Offence of r aising fund for a t errorist o rganisation. — ( 1 ) A person commits the offence of`
  line `raising fund for a terrorist organisation, who, with intention to further the activity of a terrorist`
  line `organisation, —`
  line `( a ) invites another person to provide money or other property, and intends that it should be used,`
  line `or has reasonable cause to suspect that it might be used, for the purposes of terrorism; or`
  line `( b ) receives money or other property, and intends that it should be used, or has reasonable cau se`
  line `to suspect that it might be used, for the purposes of terrorism; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 7 for “Schedule” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `( c ) provides money or other property, and knows, or has reasonable cause to suspect, that it`
  line `would or might be used for the purposes of terrorism.`
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of thi s sub - section, a reference to provide money or other property`
  line `includes —`
  line `( a ) of its being given, lent or otherwise made available, whether or not for consideration; or`
  line `( b ) raising, collecting or providing funds through production or smuggling or circulation of high`
  line `quality counterfeit Indian currency.]`
  line `( 2 ) A person, who commits the offence of raising fund for a terrorist organisation under`
  line `sub - section ( 1 ), shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term not exceeding fourteen yea rs, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `41. Continuance of a ssociation. — An association shall not be deemed to have ceased to exist by`
  line `reason only of any formal act of its dissolution or change of name but shall be deemed to continue so long`
  line `as any actual combination for the purposes of such association continues between any members thereof.`
  line `42. Power to d elegate. — The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that all or any of the powers which may be exercis ed by it under section 7, or section 8, or both, shall, in`
  line `such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised`
  line `also by any State Government and the State Government may, with the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, by order in writing, direct that any power which has been directed to be exercised by it`
  line `shall, in such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be`
  line `exercised by any person subordinate to the State Government as may be specified therein.`
  line `43. Officers c ompetent to i nvestigate o ffence s under Chapters IV and VI. — Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Code, no police officer, —`
  line `( a ) in the case of the Delhi Special Police Establishment, constituted under sub - section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 2 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946), below the rank of a`
  line `Deputy Superintendent of Police or a police officer of equivalent rank;`
  line `( b ) in the metropolitan areas of Mumbai, Kolkata, Chennai and Ahmedabad and any other`
  line `metropolitan area notified as such under sub - section ( 1 ) of section 8 of the Code, below the rank of an`
  line `Assistant Commissioner of Police;`
  line `2 [( ba ) in the case of National Investigation Agency, below the rank of Inspector];`
  line `( c ) in any case not relatable to clause ( a ) 2 [ or clause ( ba )], below the rank of a Deputy`
  line `Superintendent of Police or a police officer of an equivalent rank,`
  line `S hall investigate any offence punishable under Chapter IV or VI.`
  line `3 [ 43A. Power to arrest, search, etc. — Any officer of the Designated Authority empowered in this`
  line `behalf, by general or special order of the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may`
  line `be, knowing of a design to commit any offence under this Act or has reason to believe from pers onal`
  line `knowledge or information given by any person and taken in writing that any person has committed an`
  line `offence punishable under this Act or from any document, article or any other thing which may furnish`
  line `evidence of the commission of such offence or from any illegally acquired property or any document or`
  line `other article which may furnish evidence of holding any illegally acquired property which is liable for`
  line `seizure or freezing or forfeiture under this Chapter is kept or concealed in any building, conveyance or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2013, s. 13, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1 - 2 - 2013).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 12 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `place, may authorise any officer subordinate to him to arrest such a person or search such building,`
  line `conveyance or place whether by day or by night or himself arrest such a person or search a such building,`
  line `conveyance or place.`
  line `43B. Procedure of a rrest, seizure, etc. — ( 1 ) Any officer arresting a person under section 43A shall,`
  line `as soon as may be, inform him of the grounds for such arrest.`
  line `( 2 ) Every person arrested and article seized under section 43A shall be forwarded without`
  line `unnecessary delay to th e officer - in - charge of the nearest police station.`
  line `( 3 ) The authority or officer to whom any person or article is forwarded under sub - section ( 2 ) shall,`
  line `with all convenient dispatch, take such measures as may be necessary in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of the Code.`
  line `43C. Application of provisions of Code. — The provisions of the Code shall apply, insofar as they`
  line `are not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, to all arrests, searches and seizures made under this`
  line Act.
  line `43D. Modified application of certain provisions of the Code. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code or any other law, every offence punishable under this Act shall be deemed to be a`
  line `cognizable offence within the meaning of clause ( c ) of section 2 of the Code, and “ cognizab le case ” as`
  line `defined in that clause shall be construed accordingly.`
  line `( 2 ) Section 167 of the Code shall apply in relation to a case involving an offence punishable under`
  line `this Act subject to the modification that in sub - section ( 2 ), —`
  line `( a ) the references to “ fif teen days ”, “ ninety days ” and “ sixty days ”, wherever they occur, shall be`
  line `construed as references to “ thirty days ”, “ ninety days ” and “ ninety days ” respectively; and`
  line `( b ) after the proviso, the following provisos shall be inserted, namely: —`
  line `“ Provided further that if it is not possible to complete the investigation within the said period`
  line `of ninety days, the Court may if it is satisfied with the report of the Public Prosecutor indicating`
  line `the progress of the investigation and the specific reasons for the detention of the accused beyond`
  line `the said period of ninety days, extend the said period up to one hundred and eighty days:`
  line `Provided also that if the police officer making the investigation under this Act, requests, for`
  line `the purposes of investigation, for pol ice custody from judicial custody of any person in judicial`
  line `custody, he shall file an affidavit stating the reasons for doing so and shall also explain the delay,`
  line `if any, for requesting such police custody.`
  line `( 3 ) Section 268 of the Code shall apply in relati on to a case involving an offence punishable under`
  line `this Act subject to the modification that —`
  line `( a ) the reference in sub - section ( 1 ) thereof —`
  line `( i ) to “ the State Government ” shall be construed as a reference to “ the Central Government or`
  line `the State Government. ”;`
  line `( ii ) to “ order of the State Government ” shall be construed as a reference to “ order of the`
  line `Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be ”; and`
  line `( b ) the reference in sub - section ( 2 ) thereof, to “ the State Government ” shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to “ the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be ”.`
  line `( 4 ) Nothing in section 438 of the Code shall apply in relation to any case involving the arrest of any`
  line `person accused of having committed an offence punishable under this Act.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, no person accused of an offence punishable`
  line `under Chapters IV and VI of this Act shall, if in custody, be released on bail or on his own bond unless`
  line `the Public Prosecutor has been given an opportunity of being heard on the application for such release:`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `Provided that such accused person shall not be released on bail or on his own bond if the Court, on a`
  line `perusal of the case diary or the report made under section 173 of the Code is of the opinion that the re are`
  line `reasonable grounds for believing that the accusation against such person is prima facie true.`
  line `( 6 ) The restrictions on granting of bail specified in sub - section ( 5 ) is in addition to the restrictions`
  line `under the Code or any other law for the time being in force on granting of bail.`
  line `( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ), no bail shall be granted to a`
  line `person accused of an offence punishable under this Act, if he is not an Indian citizen and has entered the`
  line `country unauthorised ly or illegally except in very exceptional circumstances and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing.`
  line `43E. Presumption as to offence under section 15. — In a prosecution for an offence under`
  line `section 15, if it is proved —`
  line `( a ) that the arms or explosives or any other substances specified in the said section were`
  line `recovered from the possession of the accused and there is reason to believe that such arms or`
  line `explosives or other substances of a similar nature were used in the commission of such offence; or`
  line `( b ) that by the evidence of the expert the finger - prints of the accused or any other definitive`
  line `evidence suggesting the involvement of the accused in the offence were found at the site of the`
  line `offence or on anything including arms and vehicles used in connectio n with the commission of such`
  line offence,
  line `the Court shall presume, unless the contrary is shown, that the accused has committed such offence.`
  line `43F. Obligation to furnish information. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law,`
  line `the officer investigating any offence under this Act, with the prior approval in writing of an officer not`
  line `below the rank of a Superintendent of Police, may require any officer or authority of the Cent ral`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority or a bank, or a company, or a firm or any other`
  line `institution, establishment, organisation or any individual to furnish information in his or its possession in`
  line `relation to such offence, on points or m atters, where the investigating officer has reason to believe that`
  line `such information will be useful for, or relevant to, the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The failure to furnish the information called for under sub - section ( 1 ), or deliberately furnishing`
  line `false information shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or`
  line `with fine or with both.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, an offence under sub - section ( 2 ) shall be tried as`
  line `a summary case and the procedure prescribed in Chapter XXI of the said Code [except sub - section ( 2 ) of`
  line `section 262] shall be applicable thereto.]`
  line `44. Protection of w itnesses. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code, the proceedings`
  line `under this Act may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, be held in camera if the court so desires.`
  line `( 2 ) A court, if on an application made by a witness in any proceeding before it or by th e Public`
  line `Prosecutor in relation to such witness or on its own motion, is satisfied that the life of such witness is in`
  line `danger, it may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, take such measures as it deems fit for keeping the`
  line `identity and address of such wi tness secret.`
  line `( 3 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub - section ( 2 ), the`
  line `measures which a court may take under that sub - section may include —`
  line `( a ) the holding of the proceedings at a place to be decided by the court;`
  line `( b ) the avoiding of the mention of the name and address of the witness in its orders or judgments`
  line `or in any records of the case accessible to public;`
  line `( c ) the issuing of any directions for securing that the identity and address of the witness are not`
  line `discl osed;`
  line `( d ) a decision that it is in the public interest to order that all or any of the proceedings pending`
  line `before such a court shall not be published in any manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `( 4 ) Any person who contravenes any decision or direction issued under sub - section ( 3 ), shal l be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years, and shall also be liable to fine.`
  line `45. Cognizance of o ffences. — 1 [ ( 1 ) ] No court shall take cognizance of any offence —`
  line `( i ) under Chapter III without the previous sanction of the Central Government or any officer`
  line `authorised by the Central Government in this behalf;`
  line `( ii ) under Chapter IV and VI without the previous sanction of the Central Government or, as the`
  line `case may be, the State Government, and 2 [if] such offence is committed against the Government of a`
  line `foreign country without the previous sanction of the Central Government.`
  line `3 [( 2 ) Sanction for prosecution under sub - section ( 1 ) shall be given within such time as may be`
  line `presc ribed only after considering the report of such authority appointed by the Central Government or, as`
  line `the case may be, the State Government which shall make an independent review of the evidence gathered`
  line `in the course of investigation and make a recommendat ion, within such time as may be prescribed, to the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.]`
  line `46. Admissibility of e vidence c ollected t hrough the interception of c ommunications. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, the evidence collected through the interception of wire, electronic or oral`
  line `communication under the provisions of the Indian Telegraph Act, 1885 (13 of 1885) or the Information`
  line `Te chnology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000) or any other law for the time being in force, shall be admissible as`
  line `evidence against the accused in the court during the trial of a case:`
  line `Provided that the contents of any wire, electronic or oral communication intercepted or evidence`
  line `derived therefrom shall not be received in evidence or otherwise disclosed in any trial, hearing or other`
  line `proceeding in any court unless each accused has been furnished with a copy of the order of the competent`
  line `authority under the aforesaid law, under which the interception was directed, not less than ten days before`
  line `trial, hearing or proceeding:`
  line `Provided further that the period of ten days may be waived by the judge trying the matter, if he comes`
  line `to the conclusion that it was not possible to fu rnish the accused with such order ten days before the trial,`
  line `hearing or proceeding and that the accused shall not be prejudiced by the delay in receiving such order.`
  line `47. Bar of j urisdiction. — ( 1 ) Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no proceedi ng taken`
  line `under this Act by the Central Government or the District Magistrate or any officer authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the Central Government or the District Magistrate, shall be called in question in any civil court`
  line `in any suit or application or by way of appeal or revision, and no injunction shall be granted by any civil`
  line `court or other authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred`
  line `by or under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub - section ( 1 ), no civil court or other authority shall have,`
  line `or be entitled to exercise, any jurisdiction, powers or authority in relation to the matters referred to in`
  line `section 36.`
  line `48. Effect of Act and r ules, etc., inconsistent with other e nactments. — The provisions o f this Act`
  line `or any rule or order made thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith`
  line `contained in any enactment other than this Act or any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment`
  line `other than this Act.`
  line `49. Protection of a ction t ake n in g ood f aith. — No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against —`
  line `( a ) the Central Government or a State Government or any officer or authority of the Central`
  line `Government or State Government or District Magistrate or any officer authorised in this behalf by the`
  line `Government or the District Magistrate or any other authority on whom powers have been conferred`
  line `1. Section 45 renumbered as sub - section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 35 of 2008, s. 13 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 28 of 2019, s. 9 for “ where ” (w.e.f. 14 - 8 - 2019).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 13 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
