  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `under this Act, for anything which is in good faith done or purported to be done in pursuance of this`
  line `Act or any rule or order made thereunder; and`
  line `( b ) any serving or retired member of the armed forces or para - military force s in respect of any`
  line `action taken or purported to be taken by him in good faith, in the course of any operation directed`
  line `towards combating terrorism.`
  line `50. Saving. — Nothing in this Act shall affect the jurisdiction exercisable by, or the procedure`
  line `applicable to, any court or other authority under any law relating to the navy, army or air force or other`
  line `armed forces of the Union.`
  line `51. Impounding of passport and arms licence of person charge sheeted under the Act. —`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other l aw for the time being in force, the passport and the`
  line `arms licence of a person, who is charge - sheeted for having committed any offence under this Act, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been impounded for such period as the court may deem fit.`
  line `1 [ 51A. Certain powers of t he Central Government. — For the prevention of, and for coping with`
  line `terrorist activities, the Central Government shall have power to —`
  line `( a ) freeze, seize or attach funds and other financial assets or economic resources held by, on`
  line `behalf of or at the direction of the individuals or entities listed in the Schedule to the Order, or any`
  line `other person engaged in or suspected to be engaged in terrorism;`
  line `( b ) prohibit any individual or entity from making any funds, financial assets or economic`
  line `resources or rel ated services available for the benefit of the individuals or entities listed in the`
  line `Schedule to the Order or any other person engaged in or suspected to be engaged in terrorism;`
  line `( c ) prevent the entry into or the transit through India of individuals listed in the Schedule to the`
  line `Order or any other person engaged in or suspected to be engaged in terrorism.]`
  line `52. Power to m ake r ules. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing powers, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) the service of notices or orders issued or made under this Act and the manner in which such`
  line `notices or orders may be served, where the person to be served is a corporation, company, bank or`
  line `other association;`
  line `( b ) the procedure to be followed by the Tribunal or a District Judge in holding any inquiry or`
  line `disposing of any application under thi s Act;`
  line `( c ) determination of the price of the forfeited property under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 28;`
  line `( d ) the procedure for admission and disposal of an application under sub - section ( 3 ) of section 36;`
  line `( e ) the qualifications of the members of the Review Committee under sub - section ( 2 ) of section`
  line `37; and`
  line `2 [( ee ) the time within which sanction for prosecution and recommendation to the Central`
  line `Government shall be given under sub - section ( 2 ) of section 45, and]`
  line `( f ) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line `53. Orders and r ules to be l aid before both Houses of Parliament. — 3 [ ( 1 ) ] Every order and every`
  line `rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 14 (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 15, ibid., (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
  line `3. Section 53 r e numbered as sub - section ( 1 ) thereof by s. 16, ibid. (w.e.f. 3 1 - 12 - 2008 ).`
