  line 25
  line `modification in the order or rule or both Houses agree that the order or ru le should not be made, the order`
  line `or rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so,`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that order or rule.`
  line `1 [( 2 ) The Order referred to in entry 33 of the Schedule and every amendment made to that Order shall`
  line `be laid as soon as may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total`
  line `period of 30 d ays which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 35 of 2008, s. 16, (w.e.f. 31 - 12 - 2008).`
